            <fr:title text="Logicians' Weird Habit 1">Logicians' Weird Habit 1</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
             Whenever I say something like "BLAH or SUCH-AND-SUCH", I always mean to <html:em>include</html:em> the case where both BLAH and SUCH-AND-SUCH happen.
            I won't bother with any extra qualification like "or both", or anything like that.
            You can always take for granted that I mean to include the both case.
            So, for example, I'd be perfectly happy to say: "Melbourne is in Victoria or Mercury is the closest planet to the Sun".
            Both of these are true, so my "or" claim is all good.

</html:p>
